    <modellingAndValidation>
      <representativeness systemModelId="290c1f85-4cc4-4fa1-b0c8-2cb7f4276dce">
        <systemModelName xml:lang="en">Allocation, cut-off by classification</systemModelName>
        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">Data were collected from existing literature, statistics, and environmental reports. Where no country specific data was available, extrapolations or global averages served as proxy.</samplingProcedure>
        <extrapolations xml:lang="en">Inventory based on data for the energy use and emissions in the Swiss distribution network (non-verified data partly based on qualified estimates), as described in Bussa et al. (2023). The emission rate of methane (leakage) is calculated based on reported methane emissions of the Swiss distribution network for 2018. In this study, not only pipeline leakages, but also emissions due to fractures and maintenance as well as emissions at the connection point of the consumers are considered. Infrastructure requirements are based on qualified estimates.
Reference(s): 
M. Bussa, N. Jungbluth, Ch. Meili (2023) Life cycle inventories for long-distance transport and distribution of natural gas. ESU-services Ltd. Schaffhausen, Switzerland. Available from: http://esu-services.ch/data/public-lci-reports/</extrapolations>
      </representativeness>
